main event: A city patrolman observed a stationary light in the sky over Wausau, Wisconsin on March 30, 1966.
interesting points: The observed light was stationary and approximately the size of a grapefruit,The light was blueish green with flashing lights,It was observed for about 5 minutes before the observer stopped watching,Weather conditions were very clear during the sighting,The conclusion attributed the sighting to the planet Jupiter in the northeast.
witness description: A city patrolman aged 34 from Schofield, Wisconsin.
